'''Kwasi Sibo''' (born 24 June 1998) is a Ghanaian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Real Oviedo]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Club career==
Sibo began his career with Ghanaian side [[Cheetah F.C.|Cheetah FC]] before joining [[Armenian Premier League]] side [[FC Urartu|Banants]] in September 2017. The following year, he signed for [[Premier League]] side [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on a long-term deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://footballghana.com/watford-fc-sign-ghanaian-youngster-kwasi-sibo-on-a-long-term-deal|title=Watford FC sign Ghanaian youngster Kwasi Sibo on a long-term deal|website=footballghana.com|date=10 August 2018|accessdate=21 July 2020}}</ref>

In January 2019, Sibo joined [[Kategoria Superiore|Albanian Superliga]] side [[KF Skënderbeu Korçë|Skënderbeu Korçë]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/kwasi-sabo-nets-consolation-for-kf-skenderbeu-in-defeat-against-kf-tirana|title=Kwasi Sabo nets consolation for KF Skenderbeu in defeat against KF Tirana|website=ghanasoccernet.com|date=23 February 2019|accessdate=21 July 2020}}</ref> The following season he spent some time training with [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] before heading to Spain to join [[UD Ibiza|Ibiza]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibizaud.com/en/kwasi-sibo-new-ibiza-player/|title=Ibiza signs Kwasi Sibo on loan|publisher=[[UD Ibiza]]|date=1 August 2019|accessdate=21 July 2020|archive-date=12 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200912191949/https://www.ibizaud.com/en/kwasi-sibo-new-ibiza-player/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 12 August 2020, it was announced Sibo would remain on loan at the Spanish side for another season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibizaud.com/en/sibo-stays-with-ibiza-one-more-season/|title=Sibo stays with Ibiza one more season|publisher=[[UD Ibiza]]|date=12 August 2020|accessdate=16 September 2020|archive-date=30 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200830112412/https://www.ibizaud.com/en/sibo-stays-with-ibiza-one-more-season/|url-status=dead}}</ref> In August 2021, he signed permanently with [[Real Betis]], being assigned to [[Betis Deportivo Balompié|the reserves]] in [[Primera División RFEF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realbetisbalompie.es/noticias/cantera/el-betis-deportivo-incorpora-a-kwasi-sibo-26294|title=El Betis Deportivo incorpora a Kwasi Sibo|publisher=Real Betis Balompie|date=30 August 2020|accessdate=12 November 2021|language=Spanish}}</ref>

On 5 September 2022, Sibo joined [[SD Amorebieta]] also in the third division.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sdamorebieta.eus/es/kwasi-sibo-refuerza-el-centro-del-campo-de-los-azules/|title=Kwasi Sibo refuerza el centro del campo de los azules|trans-title=Kwasi Sibo bolsters the centre of midfield of the blues|publisher=SD Amorebieta|language=es|date=5 September 2022|accessdate=8 June 2023}}</ref> He helped in the club's promotion to [[Segunda División]] in [[2022–23 Primera Federación|his first season]], but suffered relegation in [[2023–24 Segunda División|his second]].

On 4 July 2024, Sibo joined [[Real Oviedo]] in the second division on a two-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realoviedo.es/noticias/kwasi-sibo-nuevo-futbolista-del-real-oviedo|trans-title=Kwasi Sibo, new Real Oviedo player|title=Kwasi Sibo, nuevo futbolista del Real Oviedo|website=www.realoviedo.es|language=Spanish|date=4 July 2024|accessdate=4 July 2024}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Sibo is the younger brother of fellow Ghanaian footballer [[Simon Zibo]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Ghanaian midfielder Kwasi Sibo joins La Liga club Real Betis - Kickgh.com|url=https://www.kickgh.com/more/ghanaians-abroad/14585-ghanaian-midfielder-kwasi-sibo-joins-la-liga-club-real-betis|access-date=2021-08-30|website=www.kickgh.com|language=en-gb|archive-date=8 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608164950/https://www.kickgh.com/more/ghanaians-abroad/14585-ghanaian-midfielder-kwasi-sibo-joins-la-liga-club-real-betis|url-status=dead}}</ref>

